\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 26. V. baumgartenii} Roemer & Schultes,{\i  Syst. Veg. }{\b 1}: 100 (1817). Stems 4-12 cm, ascending, pubescent above. Leaves 8-18 × 3-8 mm, serrate to subentire, glabrous, subsessile, the lower ovate, the upper elliptic-oblong. Racemes 1-4, opposite, short, corymbose; pedicels up to 15 mm, pubescent, greatly exceeding the bracts. Calyx 2·5-3 mm; segments 4, ellipticoblong, subequal. Corolla c. 9 mm in diameter, blue. Capsule 5 × 3 mm, elliptical, deeply emarginate, glabrous.{\i  Mountain rocks and alpine pastures. • E. & S. Carpathians; mountains of E. Jugoslavia and N. Bulgaria.} Bu Ju Rm Rs (W).
