\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 27. V. officinalis} L., {\i Sp. Pl.} 11 (1753). Stems 10-50 cm, procumbent to ascending, hirsute to villous. Leaves 15-50 × 8-30 mm, ovate to elliptical, serrate, softly hairy; petiole 2-6 mm. Racemes 3-6(-10) cm, erect, opposite, dense, glandular-hairy; pedicels 1-3 mm; bracts 3-5 mm. Calyx 2·5-3 mm; segments 4, oblong, subequal. Corolla c. 8 mm in diameter, dull lilac-blue. Capsule c. 4 × 4 mm, obdeltate to slightly obcordate, pubescent. 2n = 18, 36.{\i  Woods and heaths. Almost throughout Europe}. All except Bl Cr Sb.
\par

