\pard\f0\fs28  Variants with small, glabrous leaves, villous peduncles, deeply obcordate capsules, and sometimes with deep blue corolla are recorded from a few localities in N.W. & N.C. Europe. They are in some features transitional between {\b 27} and {\b 28}, and their status is not clear.
